stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> NOM: System Start
    
    NOM --> PEM: R > θ_R or S > θ_S<br/>Risk or stress detected
    PEM --> NOM: Sustained good behavior<br/>R < θ_R and S < θ_S
    
    PEM --> CM: Repeated violations<br/>or W[c] high
    CM --> PEM: Gradual improvement<br/>Reduced risk
    
    CM --> ISO: Severe harm<br/>or persistent adversarial
    ISO --> CM: Extended good behavior<br/>Manual review
    
    NOM: NOM (Normal)
    NOM: D = 8-12 (full depth)
    NOM: V = 2-3 (verbose)
    NOM: Tools = ALLOWED
    
    PEM: PEM (Probation)
    PEM: D = 6-10 (reduced)
    PEM: V = 1-2 (moderate)
    PEM: Tools = ALLOWED
    
    CM: CM (Containment)
    CM: D = 4-6 (minimal)
    CM: V = 0-1 (terse)
    CM: Tools = READONLY only
    
    ISO: ISO (Isolation)
    ISO: D = 2-4 (refusal)
    ISO: V = 0 (minimal)
    ISO: Tools = DISALLOWED
    
    note right of NOM
        Full capability
        Normal operation
    end note
    
    note right of PEM
        Reduced capability
        Increased monitoring
    end note
    
    note right of CM
        Minimal capability
        Heavy restrictions
    end note
    
    note right of ISO
        Refusal mode
        Manual intervention required
    end note
